    "media_with_text_Q8n9Pe": {
      "type": "media-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_jfdGgy": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Back in 2011, I was helping my sister redecorate her flat in<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wakefield\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Wakefield</span></a>. Money was tight, space was even tighter, and we’d spent hours browsing websites, showrooms, and catalogues looking for a decent bed. Everything seemed overpriced, underwhelming, or both.</p><p>Eventually, frustrated with the lack of options, we did something that would quietly change the course of my life: we built our own. Not from scratch exactly — we repurposed an old frame, added our headboard design, sourced upholstery fabric from a market in Leeds, and stitched the pieces together over a weekend.</p><p>That bed? It looked far better than anything we’d seen online. And it worked. It was simple, stylish, affordable, and — most importantly — made with care.</p><p>At the time, I didn’t think I’d just built the prototype of Bedroom King. But looking back, that moment planted a seed that never stopped growing.</p>",
            "enlarge_text": false
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_jfdGgy"
      ],
      "name": "Media with text",
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Untitled_design_21_81f33339-94fd-4596-b037-a0eef3092bbb.png",
        "video_external": "",
        "video_description": "",
        "video_autoplay": false,
        "layout": "left",
        "image_fit": "contain",
        "media_width": 50,
        "media_scale": 100,
        "text_align": "text-start",
        "color_scheme": "none"
      }
    },
    "media_with_text_HzgtkC": {
      "type": "media-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_NMWzhG": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "An Idea That Refused to Go Away",
            "heading_size": "h3",
            "heading_h1": false
          }
        },
        "text_GMiD98": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Over the next few months, word got out. Friends asked me to make beds for their flats. My uncle asked for a custom-sized base. A neighbour wanted a drawer option. There was a demand — but more than that, there was a shared frustration.</p><p>Everyone I spoke to seemed to have the same problem:</p><p>“Why is it so hard to find a good bed that doesn’t cost a fortune?”</p><p>That stuck with me. At the time, I was working full-time in logistics, but I began building beds on weekends. I spent nights researching fabrics, frames, and mechanisms. I learned about Ottoman lifts, slatted bases, and reinforced corners. I started experimenting with frames that could hold up to years of real use — kids jumping on them, people moving house, the odd spilled coffee.</p><p>Soon, the garage was full. Then the spare room. Then my mate’s unit across town.</p>",
            "enlarge_text": false
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_NMWzhG",
        "text_GMiD98"
      ],
      "name": "Media with text",
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Untitled_design_9.png",
        "video_external": "",
        "video_description": "",
        "video_autoplay": false,
        "layout": "right",
        "image_fit": "contain",
        "media_width": 50,
        "media_scale": 100,
        "text_align": "text-start",
        "color_scheme": "none"
      }
    },
    "media_with_text_AVnqbD": {
      "type": "media-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_mcRbNi": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Building Something That Lasts",
            "heading_size": "h3",
            "heading_h1": false
          }
        },
        "text_RTW8a7": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We officially launched<a href=\"https://www.bedroomking.co.uk/\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Bedroom King</span></a> in 2013, with just three models: a standard divan, a velvet ottoman, and a storage bed with drawers.</p><p>I remember the first real online sale. It came from Sheffield. A couple had seen one of our Facebook posts and messaged late at night:</p><p>“Hi, can you make this in king size with a taller headboard?”</p><p>We could. We did.</p><p>What followed were months of long days, weekend deliveries, and sourcing locally wherever we could. We didn’t have massive capital, but we had something more valuable: genuine care. Every bed that left our tiny workshop had been built and tested by someone who understood what it was like to live in a real home, with kids, pets, small rooms, and tighter budgets.</p>",
            "enlarge_text": false
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_mcRbNi",
        "text_RTW8a7"
      ],
      "name": "Media with text",
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Untitled_design_20_d4b0eed0-a69f-4a34-a9b2-4b7ff28fbe88.png",
        "video_external": "",
        "video_description": "",
        "video_autoplay": false,
        "layout": "left",
        "image_fit": "contain",
        "media_width": 50,
        "media_scale": 100,
        "text_align": "text-start",
        "color_scheme": "none"
      }
    },
    "media_with_text_4LWTLa": {
      "type": "media-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_pHDa3N": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why the Name “Bedroom King”?",
            "heading_size": "h3",
            "heading_h1": false
          }
        },
        "text_z37UwY": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Funny story — we didn’t plan to be called Bedroom King. The original name idea was “York Beds Co.”, but it didn’t stick. It sounded a bit too formal. Too forgettable.</p><p>One evening, while sketching out ideas with my brother, we joked:</p><p>“If we’re making beds fit for royalty, let’s just call it Bedroom King.”</p><p>It made us laugh. But the more we said it, the more it worked. It was bold, confident, and a bit cheeky — much like the brand we were trying to build.</p><p>We registered the domain that night. And we never looked back.</p>",
            "enlarge_text": false
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_pHDa3N",
        "text_z37UwY"
      ],
      "name": "Media with text",
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Untitled_design_26.png",
        "video_external": "",
        "video_description": "",
        "video_autoplay": false,
        "layout": "right",
        "image_fit": "contain",
        "media_width": 50,
        "media_scale": 100,
        "text_align": "text-start",
        "color_scheme": "none"
      }
    },
    "rich_text_mR4NAf": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_PWYaTa": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Growing with Our Customers",
            "heading_size": "h2",
            "heading_h1": false
          }
        },
        "text_LKhwDY": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>By 2016, we’d outgrown our first unit. Then our second. What started with a few beds a month turned into a few beds a day, then dozens. We hired more staff — most from local families, friends, and referrals.</p><p>We didn’t just grow in size. We grew in understanding.</p><p></p>",
            "enlarge_text": false
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
